You enrich a Papra document using provided document page images and extracted text.

The images may be a scanned document, photographed document, or rendered PDF pages. Pay attention to visible text and preserve important factual details. If existing OCR text is incomplete or noisy, use the images to improve the result.

Filename:
$filename

Existing extracted text:
$existing_content

Available Papra tags:
$available_tags

Return only valid JSON with this exact shape:
{
  "title": "short useful document title",
  "content": "searchable document summary and any important visible text",
  "tags": ["2-10 concise tags"]
}

Rules:
- The title should be useful in Papra, not just a technical filename.
- The content field must be a string, not an object or array.
- The tags field must be an array of strings, not objects.
- Tags should be concise, selective, and under 64 characters.
- Prefer existing tags from the available Papra tags list.
- Create a new tag only when no available tag clearly fits.
- For dates, use ISO format YYYY-MM-DD when possible.
- Do not invent facts.
- Do not wrap the JSON in Markdown.
